author: Deccan
title: D-Link launches new modem router in India
text:
Deccan Chronicle | September 29, 2015, 11.47 am IST Share Tweet Printer-friendly version Send by email The nelwy launched router is priced at Rs 4,410 for the Indian market D-Link has launched its new Dual Band wireless router with modem , which can offer high-speed Internet and wireless coverage to smart devices. With concurrent dual band 802.11ac, it brings the future of high-bandwidth wireless connectivity, allowing us to stream HD video, make Internet voice calls, and surf the web uninterrupted from anywhere in home.
An Ethernet switch provides wired connections for other devices such as a network storage, to ensure that data is always accessible. Itâ€™s stylish, easy-to-use, and comes IPv6- ready so one can keep up with the next generation of network devices. The devuce is priced at Rs 4,410 for the Indian market.
